New President Samia Suluhu led Tanzanians in mourning and paying last respects to the late former President John Pombe Magufuli. A requiem mass was held at St. Peter&rsquo;s Catholic church in Oysterbay, Dar es salaam. President Suluhu later led government officials and members of the public in viewing the body of the departed leader at uhuru Stadium in the port city of Dar es salaam